fume /fjuːm/

(fuming,fumed,fumes) 

1. N-PLURAL Fumes are the unpleasant and often unhealthy smoke and gases that are produced by fires or by things such as chemicals, fuel, or cooking. (难闻且常有害的) 烟气 

例： ...car exhaust fumes. …汽车尾气。 

2. V-T/V-I If you fume over something, you express annoyance and anger about it. 表达气愤 

例： 'It's monstrous!' Jackie fumed. “这太不像话了！”杰基表达了气愤。

